WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.312
Ariel Sharon, the Bulldozer, an

00:03.312 --> 00:04.090
unstoppable force.

00:04.090 --> 00:05.256
His legend began

00:05.256 --> 00:06.797
with sheer power.

00:06.797 --> 00:07.824
Sabra-Shatila cast

00:07.824 --> 00:09.034
a long shadow.

00:09.034 --> 00:09.840
The Temple

00:09.840 --> 00:13.392
Mount visit ignited a firestorm.

00:13.392 --> 00:15.216
During the Second Intifada, he

00:15.216 --> 00:17.347
adopted a relentless approach.

00:17.347 --> 00:17.880
A

00:17.880 --> 00:18.744
surprising shift followed:

00:18.744 --> 00:19.320
Gaza disengagement,

00:19.320 --> 00:20.482
settlers removed.

00:20.482 --> 00:22.224
His own party

00:22.224 --> 00:22.435
rebelled.

00:22.435 --> 00:23.280
He declared, "Fine, I

00:23.280 --> 00:23.808
will do it myself.

00:23.808 --> 00:24.072
" He

00:24.072 --> 00:24.667
forged Kadima.

00:24.667 --> 00:25.560
A stroke struck;

00:25.560 --> 00:28.080
eight years in a coma.

00:28.080 --> 00:29.420
He died, his Gaza legacy unresolved.

00:29.420 --> 00:30.984
His impact remains complex and debated
globally.

